## Typography

**Font family:** Poppins (loaded in `app/_layout.tsx`)
- Regular: `Poppins_400Regular`
- Medium: `Poppins_500Medium`
- SemiBold: `Poppins_600SemiBold`
- Bold: `Poppins_700Bold`

### Hierarchy

| Role | Classes | Color |
|---|---|---|
| Brand label | `text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest` | `theme.textSecondary` |
| Screen heading | `text-2xl font-bold` or `text-3xl font-bold` | `theme.textPrimary` |
| Section title | `text-lg font-semibold` | `theme.textPrimary` |
| Body | `text-base` | `theme.textPrimary` or `theme.textSecondary` |
| Caption/helper | `text-sm` | `theme.textSecondary` or `theme.textTertiary` |

## Cards & Surfaces

```tsx
<View
  className="rounded-2xl p-5"
  style={{
    backgroundColor: theme.cardBg,
    borderWidth: 1,
    borderColor: theme.cardBorder,
    shadowColor: '#000',
    shadowOpacity: theme.isDark ? 0.25 : 0.06,
    shadowRadius: 16,
    shadowOffset: { width: 0, height: 4 },
    elevation: 3,
  }}
>
```

- Large cards: `rounded-2xl`
- Smaller cards/chips: `rounded-xl`
- Shadow opacity: `0.06` (light) / `0.25` (dark)
- Use `theme.isDark` for conditional shadow/border behavior

## Buttons

### Primary CTA

```tsx
<TouchableOpacity
  className="h-14 rounded-2xl items-center justify-center"
  style={{ backgroundColor: theme.buttonPrimary }}
  activeOpacity={0.7}
>
  <Text style={{ color: theme.buttonPrimaryContrast }} className="font-semibold text-base">
    {label}
  </Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

### Secondary / Ghost

```tsx
<TouchableOpacity
  className="h-14 rounded-2xl items-center justify-center"
  style={{ borderWidth: 1, borderColor: theme.textTertiary }}
  activeOpacity={0.7}
>
  <Text style={{ color: theme.textSecondary }}>{label}</Text>
</TouchableOpacity>
```

### Touch feedback

Always `activeOpacity={0.7}` on `TouchableOpacity`.

## Form Inputs

```tsx
<View
  className="rounded-xl px-4 h-12"
  style={{
    backgroundColor: theme.inputBg,
    borderWidth: 1,
    borderColor: theme.cardBorder,
  }}
>
```

- Focus border: `theme.buttonPrimary`
- Error border: `theme.buttonDecline`
- Placeholder color: `theme.textTertiary`
- Label color: `theme.textSecondary`

## Spacing

| Usage | Class |
|---|---|
| Page horizontal padding | `px-6` |
| Page top padding | `pt-6` |
| Page bottom padding | `pb-8` |
| Between sections | `gap-6` |
| Between related items | `gap-3` or `gap-4` |
| Card internal | `p-5` or `p-8` |

## LoadingScreen

```tsx
import { LoadingScreen } from '@/components/ui/LoadingScreen';

// Always provide a translated message
if (isLoading) return <LoadingScreen message={t('common.loading')} />;
```

Uses `theme.pageBg`, `theme.buttonPrimary`, `theme.textSecondary` internally.

## Color Rules

- **Never** hardcode hex values — use `theme.*` tokens
- **Never** assume primary button text is white — use `theme.buttonPrimaryContrast`
- **Never** add purple, gold, blue, or other brand accents — black/white/grey only
- **Never** use `#ffffff` or `#000000` directly where a theme token exists
- **Always** use `theme.isDark` for conditional dark/light logic
- For quiz correct/incorrect: use `theme.quizCorrect` / `theme.quizIncorrect` (text), `theme.quizCorrectBg` / `theme.quizIncorrectBg` (background)
- For badge pills: use `theme.badgeSuccess`, `theme.badgeError`, `theme.badgeWarning`, `theme.badgeInfo`

## Gluestack Integration

The Gluestack provider config (`components/ui/gluestack-ui-provider/config.ts`) uses a greyscale primary scale. `GluestackUIProvider` is set to `mode={colorScheme ?? 'light'}` following system color scheme. Use Gluestack primitives (`Box`, `VStack`, `HStack`, `Text`, `Button`) as building blocks and customize with NativeWind classes.

## Raw Color Tokens

Source: `constants/themeTokens.ts`. Do not use these directly in components — use `useTheme()` which maps them to the correct mode:

```
primary.light = '#171717'   primary.dark = '#FAFAFA'
decline.light = '#b91c1c'   decline.dark = '#f87171'
accept.light = '#10b981'    (same for both modes)
success = '#4d7c59'
```
